# Readable UI in tools

Interactive visualizers wrap content in `.tool-surface` (via `VisualizerLayout`). Respect these floors everywhere inside tools:

| Token | Size | Use for |
|-------|------|---------|
| `--text-min-caption` | 14px | Scale labels, hints, metadata, uppercase section tags |
| `--text-min-ui` | 15px | Helper copy, secondary labels, small buttons |
| `--text-min-control` | 16px | Slider labels, primary control text |
| `--touch-min` | 44px | Buttons, slider thumbs, tappable controls |
| `--crayon-icon-min` | 36px | Crayon motif holders beside sliders |

## Do

- Use shared `<Slider />` for ranges; pass scale endpoints via the `marks` prop (renders `.crayon-slider__marks` at caption size).
- Use `text-sm` or larger for helper sentences learners must read.
- Prefer semantic sizes (`text-sm`, `text-base`) — `.tool-surface` bumps undersized utilities automatically.

## Don't

- `text-[10px]`, `text-[11px]`, or `text-xs` for primary instructional copy (captions only).
- Tiny icon-only controls under 36px beside sliders.
- One-off pixel font sizes when a design token exists.

New tool UI should be authored assuming `.tool-surface` is active; do not rely on 12px text “looking fine” on desktop.
